Wash and dry all produce. Bring a #medium pot{} of @salt{} water to a boil. Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Pat @chicken breasts{24%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{} and season all over with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and 2 tsp @Tuscan heat spice{2%tsp} (save the rest for step 4). Add to pan and cook until no longer pink in center, ~{5-8%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Lower heat to medium if surface starts to blacken before meat is cooked through.

Remove chicken from pan and set aside to rest.

Once water boils, add @gemelli pasta{6%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{10-12%minutes}. While gemelli cooks, pick half the @basil{½%ounce} from stems (leave the remainder on the stem and save for lunch).

Roughly chop picked leaves or tear into smaller pieces with your hands. Once gemelli is done, scoop out and reserve ¼ cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

> TIP: Don't put away the pot just yet; we'll use it later.

Cut @fresh mozzarella{4%ounce} and @roma tomato{2} into 1/2-inch pieces. Place half the tomatoes and all of the mozzarella in a #reusable container{}. Add 2 tsp @red wine vinegar{2%tsp} and 2 tsp @pesto{2%tsp} (we'll use more vinegar and pesto later). Once chicken is cool enough to touch, cut half (2 breasts) into bite-sized pieces. Add cut chicken to container, toss to combine, and keep refrigerated until you're ready to prep lunch in the morning.

Heat a drizzle of oil in #pan used for chicken{} over medium heat. Add @sugar{1%tsp} and remaining @roma tomato{}(1, diced), @Tuscan heat spice{1%tsp}, and @red wine vinegar{1%tsp} to pan. Cook until vinegar and any juices have thickened slightly, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and 3 TBSP water. Bring to a simmer, then remove pan from heat. Stir in @butter{3%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

Return drained gemelli to #pot{} and place over low heat, then stir in @butter{2%tbsp}, remaining @pesto{2%tsp}, and a splash of reserved pasta cooking water.

> TIP: If pasta seems dry, add more water as needed.

Season with plenty of salt and pepper. Divide remaining chicken breasts between plates and spoon tomato sauce over top. Add pasta to the side and sprinkle with @Parmesan cheese{¼%cup}. Garnish with chopped basil and serve.

The next morning, pick remaining basil leaves from stems. Tear leaves into smaller pieces and toss into reserved chicken salad in container. Fill @flour tortillas{2} with chicken salad, roll into wraps, pack, and refrigerate before enjoying cold or at room temperature.

> TIP: If you've got a little while before you eat, divide the chicken salad between two containers, pack each with a tortilla, and wrap before enjoying (the wrap may not hold together if left for too long).